[2026-03-18T18:04:30.315Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017knzeYHPmhXfdey86aqbGa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All type checks pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Refactored crypto audit from opt-in callbacks to structural interceptor pattern:**\n\n1. **`packages/shared/src/auditedCrypto.ts`** (new) — Defines `CryptoService` interface, `CryptoAuditEmitter` interface, and `createAuditedCryptoService()` factory. Every `encrypt`/`decrypt` call through this service automatically emits a `CryptoAuditEvent` with operation type, success/failure, error details, and caller-supplied context. It's structurally impossible to perform a crypto operation through this service without producing an audit record.\n\n2. **`packages/shared/src/index.ts`** — Added `auditedCrypto` export.\n\n3. **`packages/orchestrator/src/tokenManager.ts`** — No longer imports raw `encrypt`/`decrypt` or `deriveMasterKey`. Accepts a `CryptoService` instead of a master key string, and passes audit context (`purpose: 'claude_token'`) with every operation.\n\n4. **`packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts`** — Replaced `masterKey: Buffer` with `crypto: CryptoService`. The `setCryptoService()` method replaces `setMasterKey()`. Credential decryption now passes rich context (credentialId, credentialName, executionId, personaId) to every `decrypt` call.\n\n5. **`packages/orchestrator/src/index.ts`** — Wires up the `CryptoAuditEmitter` (logging to pino), creates the `AuditedCryptoService` once, and passes it to both `tokenManager` and `dispatcher`. The master key is derived once and captured inside the service — no raw key is passed around.\n\n**Key design property:** The O(n) verification problem (\"did every call site remember to audit?\") is now an O(1) guarantee — code that needs crypto gets it through `CryptoService`, which structurally cannot skip audit."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input